SIMPLE: reversionary
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reversionary
<hw>Re*ver"sion*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to a reversion; involving a reversion; to be
enjoyed in succession, or after the termination of a particular estate;
<as>as, a <ex>reversionary</ex> interest or right</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reversionary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Reversionary
<hw>Re*ver"sion*a*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>That
which is to be received in reversion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reversioner</ent>⟦br⟧
